div.p: Requirement: Immediately upon entering CLONE_NEWNS, the runtime must execute: mount(NULL, "/", NULL, MS_REC | MS_PRIVATE, NULL);

ol.li: Most distros (systemd) mark / as MS_SHARED by default.
Without this reset, any mount() inside the container (e.g., /proc) leaks back to the host, appearing in the host's mount table.
MS_REC ensures every existing sub-mount is also decoupled.

div.p: Flag: MS_SHARED Use Case: Peer namespaces sharing a volume.
Flag: MS_PRIVATE Use Case: Container root isolation.
Flag: MS_SLAVE Use Case: Host-managed configuration updates.
Flag: MS_UNBINDABLE Use Case: Avoiding recursive mount loops.
